  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2006-11-16",
    "date": "2006-11-30T22:31:02Z",
    "text": "Accurate Crime Trends for Schools Act or the ACT for Schools Act - Directs the Attorney General to study and report to the appropriate congressional committees on the feasibility of expanding the National Incident-Based Reporting System to include information on the occurrence of school-related crime in elementary and secondary schools.\n\nRequires the study to identify and evaluate methods for collecting and reporting such information."
